<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<div type="attributeDocumentation" xml:id="attr-base" xmlns:eac="http://archivists.org/ns/eac/v2" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ead="https://archivists.org/ns/ead/v4">
               <head>
                  <att>base</att>
               </head>
               <div type="fullName">
                  <p>Base</p>
               </div>
               <div type="summary">
                  <p>Optional attribute used to specify a base URI that is different to the base URI of the EAC-CPF instance.</p>
               </div>
               <div type="description">
                  <p>Using the optional attribute <att>base</att> allows any relative URIs provided on attributes of a specific element, or its descendants, to be resolved using the URI provided in that element's or its parent element's <att>base</att>.</p>
                  <p>Available on <gi>alternativeSet</gi>,
                     <gi>control</gi>, <gi>cpfDescription</gi>, <gi>description</gi>,
                     <gi>eac</gi>, <gi>identity</gi>, <gi>multipleIdentities</gi>,
                     <gi>relations</gi>, and <gi>sources</gi>.</p>
               </div>
               <div type="datatype">
                  <p>anyURI</p>
               </div>
